External Knowledge:
- "most highly rated talks" refers to talks with the highest average rating; 
- Average rating is the sum of ratings divided by the number of ratings.

sql:
SELECT event_name
FROM events
ORDER BY event_name;

SELECT event_id, COUNT(talk_id) AS talk_count
FROM talks
GROUP BY event_id;

SELECT AVG(rating) AS average_rating, COUNT(*) AS review_count
FROM event_reviews
WHERE event_id = 123;
